title: 50 Reasons Why Galaxy Note 4 is Better Than iPhone 6 Plus
description: In this video i will give you 50 Unique Reason's which makes Samsung Galaxy Note 4 a better choice over the Apple iPhone 6 Plus. Samsung Galaxy Note 4 comes with a 5.7" Quad HD SuperAmoled HD Display with over 500+ ppi display. Under the hood we have a Snapdragon 805 or Exynos 5433 Super fast chipset. Galaxy Note 4 also has a 16MP Camera on the back with Dual Led flash which can record 4K video recording. 3220mAh battery is on board with Micro SD Card slot option. The iPhone 6 Plus is Apple's largest smartphone ever, with a 5.5-inch display and a resolution of 1080 x 1920 pixels -- good for a pixel density of 401 ppi. The rest of the highlights of Apple's first phablet include a 64-bit dual-core A8 processor with an M8 co-processor, an 8-megapixel iSight camera with optical image stabilization and a two-tone LED flash, and, for the first time for an Apple device -- an NFC chip that facilitates mobile payments through the company's Apple Pay service.
